<p>The nominative case is used for the subject of the sentence. The subject is the thing that is 'doing' the action.</p>

<%= render '/table.*', {
  headers: [
    "Masc.", "Fem.", "Neu.", "Pl."
  ],
  rows: [
    ["", "der/ein", "die/eine", "das/ein", "die"]
  ],
} %>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<ul>
  <li><%= definite_article(das('Mädchen'), :n) %> spielt Klavier.</li>
  <li><%= definite_article(der('Hund'), :n) %> schläft.</li>
  <li><%= definite_article(die('Gans'), :n) %> ist wirklich wütend.</li>
</ul>

<p>It is also used after <b>sein</b> (to be) and <b>werden</b> (to become):</p>
<ul>
  <li>Er ist <%= nom 'ein' %> guter Lehrer.</li>
  <li>Das wird <%= indefinite_article(der('Pullover'), :n) %></li>
</ul>
